        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1970-09-23T14:52:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1970-09-23T14:52:00-05:00" n="321"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                <head>321. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Jordan</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d321fn1">Source: National Archives, <gloss
                            target="#t_RG1">RG</gloss> 59, Central Files 1970–73, AV 12. Secret;
                        Immediate. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_STW1">Seelye</persName> and
                        Alfred D. White, and approved by <persName corresp="#p_STW1"
                            >Seelye</persName>. It was repeated Priority to Beirut, Bonn, Bern,
                        London, Geneva, and Tel Aviv.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1970-09-23T19:52:00+00:00">September 23, 1970,
                        1952Z</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>156385. Ref: Tel Aviv 5318.<note n="2" xml:id="d321fn2">
                        <ref target="#d319">Document 319</ref>.</note> Subject: Hijacking Hostages.
                    While we are confident <gloss target="#t_GOJ1">GOJ</gloss> has welfare of
                    hostages very much in mind, Embassy should, unless it perceives objection, urge
                    Jordanians to provide for release of hijack hostages in any settlement with
                    Fedayeen as proposed <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWP1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Rogers</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
